No-Bake Apple Crisp For One
  --America's Test Kitchen

Filling:
1 apple, peeled, cored, and cut into 3/4" pieces
2 tbsp sugar
1 tsp lemon juice
1/8 tsp ground cinnamon

Combine apple, sugar, lemon juice, and cinnamon in bowl and microwave until apple has softened and juices have thickened, 3-4 min, stirring occasionally. Set aside to cool slightly.

Topping:
1 tbsp ap flour
1 1/2 tsp sugar
1 1/2 tsp old-fashioned rolled oats
pinch table salt
1/2 tbsp unsalted butter, cut into 2 pieces

Meanwhile, mix our, sugar, oats, and salt together in second bowl. Using fingers, rub butter into our mixture until mixture has texture of coarse crumbs. Microwave until topping is golden, ~2 min, stirring every 30 s. Sprinkle topping over apple and serve.


Notes: Golden delicious apples or any sweet crunchy ones
